Get Started with the Intro Template Bot

The Einstein Bot Intro Template is designed to get you up and running with Einstein Bots as quickly as possible. This guide provides examples of common sales and service automation scenarios that you can customize for your business.

The Intro Template covers common major use cases for your customers, including:

* Connect with Sales
* Report an Issue
* Check Issue Status
* Check Order Status
* Gather Info from User
* Supporting Dialogs

To create a bot using the Intro Template, read more at Create a New Intro Template Bot.

The template includes popular Salesforce actions such as creating a case, creating a lead, looking up an order, or adding a case comment to an existing case. It also includes intent data to kickstart conversational experiences.

This guide explains each component and best practices used to implement it, with the goal of helping you create great bots that provide a good experience for your customers.

Create an Intro Template Bot

The intro template includes popular Salesforce actions such as creating a case, creating a lead, looking up an order, or adding a case comment to an existing case. To kickstart conversational experiences, the template also includes intent data.

Learn About the Template Bot: Welcome Dialogs
* Learn about how the bot kicks off the conversation and guides the end user towards common tasks.
* Build a bot to capture end user information and create a lead record.

Learn About the Template Bot: Supporting Dialogs
* Bots work best with supporting dialogs that help create a great customer experience. 
* Learn about key dialogs: Agent Transfer, Anything else, Clear Memory, Confused, and End Chat. Explore intent data used for exact matching.
title: Einstein Bots Template Guide
